    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think this would fit better as an issue in the Solidity repo regarding the [Solidity Style Guide](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/blob/develop/docs/style-guide.rst). Events are specific to Solidity (the actual language in the yellow paper is *logs*) and naming conventions for languages that compile to EVM bytecode fit under preferred styling and not so much as an EIP. I believe the accepted convention that events begin with a capital letter avoids function confusion, but there may still be confusion with similarly capitalized constructors, so reposting this in the Solidity repo for discussion may be useful.",
